New Records: Travis Head scored a career-best 154 not out
Key Match Events: Australia chased down 316 to win the 1st ODI
England's final seven wickets fell for 83 runs
Marnus Labuschagne took 3 wickets for 39 runs
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Head stated, 'I've worked extremely hard over a few years and I probably play the game a bit more relaxed now.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was Australia's 13th straight victory in the 50-over format
Others: Ben Dwarshuis sustained a suspected pectoral strain during the match and did not return to the field
